he idea is that you select data set from tissues\\/organs of interest and in general (training set) and that you provide data set of cells (test set) differentiated towards one of the tissues\\/organs included in the training set. KeyGenes will provide the samples in the test set with an identity score to the samples that have been included in the training set. Therefore, it is very important to choose your training set carefully. Moreover, KeyGenes uses the top 500 most variably expressed genes. This top 500 list should also be carefully selected depending on the training set used.<\\/p>\"}','{\"status\":\"draft\",\"question_name\":\"What is KeyGenes?\",\"question\":\"What is KeyGenes?\",\"answer\":\"<p>KeyGenes is an algorithm to predict the identity and provide you with an identity score for the queried samples. It uses transcriptional profiles of the queried data (test set) and matches them to chosen sets of transcriptional profiles (training set).\\u2028The idea is that you select data set from tissues\\/organs of interest and in general (training set) and that you provide data set of cells (test set) differentiated towards one of the tissues\\/organs included in the training set. KeyGenes will provide the samples in the test set with an identity score to the samples that have been included in the training set. Therefore, it is very important to choose your training set carefully. Moreover, KeyGenes uses the top 500 most variably expressed genes. This top 500 list should also be carefully selected depending on the training set used.<\\/p>\"}',NULL,NULL,NULL),(840,172,'faqs','2','{\"question\":\"I am having problems to download the R-package \\u201cglmnet \\u201d version 1.9-8. What can I do?\",\"id\":\"2\",\"status\":\"published\",\"created_by\":\"1\",\"created_on\":\"2019-09-18 13:52:06\",\"question_name\":\"\\u201cglmnet \\u201d version 1.9-8. What can I do?\",\"answer\":\"<p>The package \\u201cglmnet \\u201d version 1.9-8 is not available for all the versions of R and it is not always compatible with all the versions of the packages downloaded before. For that reason, we provide a new set of versions that can be used together:<\\/p><p> R version 2.15.3 (2013-03-01)<\\/p><p> glmnet_1.9-5<\\/p><p> ggplot2_0.9.3.1<\\/p><p> gplots_2.11.0<\\/p><p> limma_3.14.4<\\/p>\"}','{\"status\":\"published\",\"question_name\":\"\\u201cglmnet \\u201d version 1.9-8. What can I do?\",\"question\":\"I am having problems to download the R-package \\u201cglmnet \\u201d version 1.9-8. What can I do?\",\"answer\":\"<p>The package \\u201cglmnet \\u201d version 1.9-8 is not available for all the versions of R and it is not always compatible with all the versions of the packages downloaded before. For that reason, we provide a new set of versions that can be used together:<\\/p><p> R version 2.15.3 (2013-03-01)<\\/p><p> glmnet_1.9-5<\\/p><p> ggplot2_0.9.3.1<\\/p><p> gplots_2.11.0<\\/p><p> limma_3.14.4<\\/p>\"}',NULL,NULL,NULL),(841,173,'faqs','1','{\"question\":\"What is KeyGenes?\",\"id\":\"1\",\"status\":\"published\",\"created_by\":\"1\",\"created_on\":\"2019-09-18 13:51:34\",\"question_name\":\"What is KeyGenes?\",\"answer\":\"<p>KeyGenes is an algorithm to predict the identity and provide you with an identity score for the queried samples. It uses transcriptional profiles of the queried data (test set) and matches them to chosen sets of transcriptional profiles (training set).\\u2028The idea is that you select data set from tissues\\/organs of interest and in general (training set) and that you provide data set of cells (test set) differentiated towards one of the tissues\\/organs included in the training set. KeyGenes will provide the samples in the test set with an identity score to the samples that have been included in the training set. Therefore, it is very important to choose your training set carefully. Moreover, KeyGenes uses the top 500 most variably expressed genes. This top 500 list should also be carefully selected depending on the training set used.<\\/p>\"}','{\"status\":\"published\"}',NULL,NULL,NULL),(842,174,'faqs','3','{\"question\":\"I do not know R. Can I still use KeyGenes?\",\"id\":\"3\",\"status\":\"published\",\"created_by\":\"1\",\"created_on\":\"2019-09-18 13:56:42\",\"question_name\":\"I do not know R. Can I still use KeyGenes?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Yes, a Web App is provided but it is at the moment limited to the use of \\u201cfixed\\u201d training sets of human transcriptional data. In that Web App, a test set can be uploaded and one of the provided \\u201cfixed\\u201d training sets can be selected. At the moment the WebApp is also limited to the use of NGS-derived data. Choosing a \\u201cflexible\\u201d training set at the moment is not possible using the Web App.<\\/p>\"}','{\"status\":\"published\",\"question_name\":\"I do not know R. Can I still use KeyGenes?\",\"question\":\"I do not know R. Can I still use KeyGenes?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Yes, a Web App is provided but it is at the moment limited to the use of \\u201cfixed\\u201d training sets of human transcriptional data. In that Web App, a test set can be uploaded and one of the provided \\u201cfixed\\u201d training sets can be selected. At the moment the WebApp is also limited to the use of NGS-derived data. Choosing a \\u201cflexible\\u201d training set at the moment is not possible using the Web App.<\\/p>\"}',NULL,NULL,NULL),(843,175,'faqs','4','{\"question\":\"Can I use KeyGenes on a microarray-derived test set?\",\"id\":\"4\",\"status\":\"draft\",\"created_by\":\"1\",\"created_on\":\"2019-09-18 13:58:59\",\"question_name\":\"Can I use KeyGenes on a microarray-derived test set?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Although KeyGenes was designed for NGS-data, it can be applied on a microarray-derived test set by using Script 3. However, microarray-derived data of tissues\\/organs from Affymetrix and Illumina platforms have been tested only using the training set \\u201cfetal\\u201d. Microarray-derived data of differentiated cells have not been tested with other training sets, and therefore, the results should be interpreted with care. See section 2.3. for more information.\\u2028In addition, we also suggest to use http:\\/\\/cellnet.hms.harvard.edu\\/ for that.<\\/p>\"}','{\"status\":\"draft\",\"question_name\":\"Can I use KeyGenes on a microarray-derived test set?\",\"question\":\"Can I use KeyGenes on a microarray-derived test set?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Although KeyGenes was designed for NGS-data, it can be applied on a microarray-derived test set by using Script 3. However, microarray-derived data of tissues\\/organs from Affymetrix and Illumina platforms have been tested only using the training set \\u201cfetal\\u201d. Microarray-derived data of differentiated cells have not been tested with other training sets, and therefore, the results should be interpreted with care. See section 2.3. for more information.\\u2028In addition, we also suggest to use http:\\/\\/cellnet.hms.harvard.edu\\/ for that.<\\/p>\"}',NULL,NULL,NULL),(844,176,'faqs','4','{\"question\":\"Can I use KeyGenes on a microarray-derived test set?\",\"id\":\"4\",\"status\":\"published\",\"created_by\":\"1\",\"created_on\":\"2019-09-18 13:58:59\",\"question_name\":\"Can I use KeyGenes on a microarray-derived test set?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Although KeyGenes was designed for NGS-data, it can be applied on a microarray-derived test set by using Script 3. However, microarray-derived data of tissues\\/organs from Affymetrix and Illumina platforms have been tested only using the training set \\u201cfetal\\u201d. Microarray-derived data of differentiated cells have not been tested with other training sets, and therefore, the results should be interpreted with care. See section 2.3. for more information.\\u2028In addition, we also suggest to use http:\\/\\/cellnet.hms.harvard.edu\\/ for that.<\\/p>\"}','{\"status\":\"published\"}',NULL,NULL,NULL),(845,177,'faqs','5','{\"question\":\"My data is annotated with other than Ensembl Gene IDs. Can I stil